-- Egypt Offers 100,000 Tons of Rice for Export, Mena Says
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2012-10-09T13:00:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-09/egypt-offers-100-000-tons-of-rice-for-export-mena-says-1-.html
Egypt  is offering 100,000 metric tons
of rice for shipment in October and November, state-run  Middle
East News Agency  reported, citing Industry and Foreign Trade
Minister Hatem Saleh.  The ministry will allow each supplier to export no more
than 15,000 tons and shipment offers will be accepted at the
ministry between Oct. 10 and Oct. 18, Mena reported, citing
Saleh. Rice shipments were allowed to resume on Oct. 1 following
a ban set in March 2008.  Egypt’s rice production in 2012 is expected to increase by
4 percent to 5.9 million tons compared with 5.67 million tons
last year, according to data on the United Nation’s Food &
Agriculture Organization’s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal in Cairo at 
